{"data": {"repository": {"pullRequest": {"id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NTQxNjQ1NzY4", "number": 2332, "title": "Use normal filesystem-based Gradle paths.", "bodyText": "I recently found that I had to rely on a sneaky ordering constraint to handle our name mangling\nhttps://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-java/blob/master/settings.gradle#L73\nAnd in #2295 I found replace(logging- to be causing problems too. I think in general using the filesystem for Gradle paths is more intuitive (just type what's on the path) and it brings more consistency with the java instrumentation repo. So finally have replaced the project name mangling with group-scoped archivesBaseName mangling instead.\nAlso fixed an issue where our BOM contains non-published artifacts too - not super-harmful but a bit weird.", "createdAt": "2020-12-17T06:45:33Z", "url": "https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-java/pull/2332", "merged": true, "mergeCommit": {"oid": "6954d1f624a1c31e0f2b2a3c073b6aae15570d40"}, "closed": true, "closedAt": "2020-12-18T03:07:34Z", "author": {"login": "anuraaga"}, "timelineItems": {"totalCount": 7, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABdm9vo2AH2gAyNTQxNjQ1NzY4OmQxZjlhYTM2MmViZmM1YWVmZTk2MmRmNzY4ODk2ZjM5NDI0MTM1ZWU=", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABdnOOS5AFqTU1NTEyMDg5NQ==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "d1f9aa362ebfc5aefe962df768896f39424135ee", "author": {"user": {"login": "anuraaga", "name": "Anuraag Agrawal"}}, "url": "https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-java/commit/d1f9aa362ebfc5aefe962df768896f39424135ee", "committedDate": "2020-12-17T06:42:36Z", "message": "Use normal filesystem-based Gradle paths."}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "5b4d353569c0b65c0b7771d59d28450b88ac1b96", "author": {"user": {"login": "anuraaga", "name": "Anuraag Agrawal"}}, "url": "https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-java/commit/5b4d353569c0b65c0